{
  "stem": "322.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And of course, out of all of us, my father, my brother, and my mother and my two sisters, I'm the only one that survived.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was in Auschwitz in-- when we arrived-- May, June, July.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then in-- then from there, I was in a Stammlager in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Stammlager is the main camp, which is to be like that I'm not a bypasser.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I, I was assigned to, permanently to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But then, then they-- yeah, I was tattooed, of course, yes, in Auschwitz-- A4685.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] then Otto Moll-- I, I know the name is not very familiar to many people, but to historians and others know very well who Otto Moll was and what he stood for, who he was in particular.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was in charge of the cremation.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He was in charge of the pits, primarily.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Otto Moll was a German, yes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because he was assigned-- after the annihilation of the Hungarian Jewry, which ended, I would say, around the end of July, beginning of August, he was assigned to become the commandant of a subcamp of Auschwitz called Gleiwitz I.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was in that subcamp until--",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Oh, of course, well, there's-- he was a Nazi, of course.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But he also, he, he was an SS man who had a very powerful role in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because when the time came to, to destroy the evidence of the existence of the gas chambers at Auschwitz and Birkenau, especially Birkenau, he was assigned to destroy, to level the-- all the gas chambers and crematoria.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was called the Otto Moll Plan, or the Moll Plan-- that's what it was called.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And of course, these things I did not know as well as I know now, for a very good reason.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
